main event: Multiple observations of a bright fireball were reported in Duluth, Minnesota on September 5 and 8, 1965.
interesting points: Reports included sightings of a fireball moving erratically across the sky,The object was described as bright with a vapor trail,There was no sound during its flight, but a loud boom was heard after it disappeared,Some witnesses observed the fireball from their vehicles while driving,The event occurred during clear weather conditions.
witness description: Observers included both civilians and military personnel.
